Twitter Expands Direct Message Search to All Users

   Tuesday October 1, 2019 2:08 pm PDT by Juli Clover
   Twitter today announced that its Direct Message (DM) search feature is
   now available to all users, allowing anyone to search through the DMs
   they've received.
   The new search bar is located above the the DM interface in the Twitter
   app or on the web and it can be used to locate specific conversations
   and key words.
   DM search first debuted in August, when Twitter said that it was
   testing out the feature. Some users have had the search bar since then
   as part of the test, but as of today, it's available for everyone.

     Get your search on. DM search is rolling out to everyone on iOS
     today.
     — Twitter (@Twitter) October 1, 2019

   Twitter can be downloaded from the App Store for free. [Direct Link]
